ow), 8, pp. 26-27; Kuiken, T., Leighton, F.A., Fouchier, R.A.M., LeDuc, J.W., Peiris, J.S.M., Schudel, A., Stohr, K., Osterhaus, A.D.M.E., Pathogen surveillance in animals (2005) Science, 309 (5741), pp. 1680-1681. , DOI 10.1126/science.1113310; Kummeneje, K., Diseases in reindeer in northern Norway (1980) Proceedings of the Symposium of the Second International Reindeer-Caribou Symposium on Roros 17-21 September Part B 1979, pp. 456-458. , Norway; Kumpula, J., Colpaert, A., Nieminen, M., The summer pasture resources of the Finnish reindeer management area (1999) Kala- Ja Riistaraportteja (Fish and Game Reports), , 152. Riistan ja kalantutkimus (Finnish Game and Fish Research Institute), Kaamanen (In Finnish with English abstract); Kutz, S.J., Hoberg, E.P., Nagy, J., Polley, L., Elkin, B., ""Emerging"" parasitic infections in Arctic ungulates (2004) Integrative and Comparative Biology, 44, pp. 109-118. , 10.1093/icb/44.2.109 10.1093/icb/44.2.109; Kutz, S.J., Hoberg, E.P., Polley, L., Jenkins, E.J., Global warming is changing the dynamics of Arctic host-parasite systems (2005) Proceedings of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences, 272 (1581), pp. 2571-2576. , DOI 10.1098/rspb.2005.3285; Kutz, S.J., Dobson, A.P., Hoberg, E.P., Where are the parasites? (2009) Science, 326, pp. 1187-1188. , 10.1126/science.326.5957.1187-b 1:CAS:528:DC%2BD1MXhsFGntrbI; Kutz, S.J., Jenkins, E.J., Veitch, A.M., Ducrocq, J., Polley, L., Elkin, B., Lair, S., The Arctic as a model for anticipating, preventing, and mitigating climate change impacts on host-parasite interactions (2009) Veterinary Parasitology, 163, pp. 217-228. , 10.1016/j.vetpar.2009.06.008; Laaksonen, S., Kuusela, J., Nikander, S., Nylund, M., Oksanen, A., Outbreak of parasitic peritonitis in reindeer in Finland (2007) The Veterinary Record, 160, pp. 835-841. , 1:STN:280:DC%2BD2szmtVaiug%3D%3D; Laaksonen, S., Solismaa, M., Orro, T., Saari, S., Kortet, R., Oksanen, A., Setaria tundra microfilariae in reindeer and other cervi